value.dp_description: The Darwin Reference Surfaces bathymetry survey was acquired for the Australian Hydrographic Office (AHO) on 8 Jul 2020. This surface was created from a contracted national reference survey in Darwin NT, collected for the purpose of calibrating multibeam echosounders. It was conducted for the Australian Hydrographic Office as part of the Hydroscheme Industry Partnership Program, acquired using R2Sonic 2026 and R2Sonic 2024, and processed using QPS Qimera. Separate grids in 0.5m resolution are provided for the two surveyed sites within this survey area in MSL, LAT and Ellipsoid vertical datum. The dataset was then exported as a 0.5m resolution, 32 bit floating point GeoTIFF grid of the survey area. This dataset is not to be used for navigational purposes.
value.dp_publisher: Department of Industry Science and Resources - Geoscience Australia
value.dp_purpose: The Australian Hydrographic Office is responsible for the publication and distribution of nautical charts and information required for the safety of ships navigating in Australian waters.  The HydroScheme Industry Partnership Program is the commercial acquisition program that undertakes focused hydrographic survey activities to contribute to national charting priorities.  This bathymetric dataset is a part of the hydrographic survey published through AusSeabed to support non-navigational use.

value.dp_description: The Northern Approaches to Broome multibeam survey was acquired for the Australian Hydrographic Office (AHO) onboard the MV Bhagwan K during the period 05 August– 02 October 2020. This was a contracted survey conducted by EGS as part of the Hydroscheme Industry Partnership Program. The survey area encompasses the northern approaches to Broome, WA located between the Talboys Rock and Gantheaume Point, Western Australia. The dataset was then exported as a 30m resolution, 32 bit floating point GeoTIFF grid of the survey area.This dataset is not to be used for navigational purposes.

value.dp_description: The Australian Immunisation Register (AIR) is a national register which records vaccines given to all people in Australia. value.dp_disposal: Record Authority 2017/00190398. Retain as per national archives.
value.dp_purpose: Purposes of the AIR are outlined in the legislation and include: maintaining an electronic database of records relating to vaccinations of individuals; collecting, analysing and publishing statistics, and other information, about vaccination coverage; monitoring vaccination coverage; monitoring the effectiveness of vaccines and vaccination programs in preventing vaccine preventable diseases; identifying any parts of Australia at risk during disease outbreaks; checking an individual’s vaccination status; advising an individual when they are due to receive doses of a vaccine; certifying when a course of vaccination has been completed; promoting health and well‑being by giving information on new developments associated with vaccinations; facilitating payments relating to vaccinations, and supporting research relating to vaccinations.

value.dp_description:
Since 1991, data was collected and reported on disability support services in Australia have been provided under four national disability agreements.
The Commonwealth/State Disability Agreement Minimum Data Set (CSDA MDS) collection was set up as a 'snapshot' data collection in 1994, following the signing of the first CSDA in 1991.
The second CSDA, signed in 1998, reflected significant changes which meant the CSDA MDS collection needed to be redesigned, including changing the collection to be a full year data collection.
In 2002-03, the redeveloped CSDA MDS became the Commonwealth State/Territory Disability Agreement National Minimum Data Set (CSTDA NMDS), and the first full financial year of data collection took place between 1 July 2003 and 30 June 2004.
The National Disability Agreement (NDA) replaced the CSTDA on 1 January 2009. As a result of the implementation of the NDA, from 2009-10 the CSTDA NMDS was renamed the DS NMDS.
From 1 July 2013, state and territory-based disability support services provided under the NDA were progressively transitioned over to the National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS). This has meant that 2018-19 was the last year for which DS NMDS was data collected and reported.
value.dp_legalauthority: Australian Institute of Health and Welfare Act 1987
value.dp_title: Disability Services National Minimum Data Set (DS NMDS)

value.dp_description:
This is a research data collection. The Bureau of Meteorology's Compact Polarimetry 2 (CP2) Research Radar operated at Redbank Plains (27°40.0'S, 152°51.5'E), Queensland from 2007-2015. This unique system collected simultaneous polarimetric observations at S-band and X-band, providing a unique dataset for quantifying precipitation properties.

The radar was used for two field campaigns, the Southeast Queensland Cloud Seeding Research Program (CSRP) from December 2007 - March 2008 and November 2008 - February 2009 , and the Coastal Convective Interactions Experiment (CCIE) from 2012 - 2014. Outside of field campaigns, six-minute volumetic scans were performed to compliment the local operational radar coverage (Mt Stapylton; 40 km to the east-southeast), providing dual Doppler coverage across much of the South East Queensland region.

This subcollection is separated into a number of products that relate to the level of processing applied.
dp_keyword: OBSERVATIONS -- Spatial Observations -- Atmospheric Domain -- Radar
value.dp_title: Compact Polarimetry 2 (CP2) research radar - simultaneous polarimetric observations at S-band and X-band

value.dp_description: This is a research data collection. The Australian Community Climate Earth System Simulator - Seasonal 1 (ACCESS-S1) is the Australian Bureau of Meteorologys seasonal prediction system used for multi-week and seasonal prediction. The archive provides access to the hindcast set i.e., forecasts run retrospectively for dates in the past. The hindcast set consists of an 11 member ensemble from the 1st, 9th, 17th, and 25th of every month for the period 1990-2012. ACCESS-S1 is based on the UK Met Office GloSea5-GC2 seasonal prediction system, but has enhancements to the ensemble generation strategy to make it appropriate for multi-week forecasting. The global coupled model includes high resolution atmospheric (N216 which is ~60 km in the mid-latitudes; and 85 levels in the vertical) and ocean (0.25 degree with 75 levels) models, as well as multi-layer land and sea-ice models.
dp_keyword: MODELLED AND PROCESSED DATA -- Numerical Weather Prediction (NWP) Gridded Output -- Atmospheric
EARTH SCIENCE SERVICES -- models -- weather research/forecast models
value.dp_title: The Australian Community Climate Earth System Simulator - Seasonal, v1 (ACCESS-S1) hindcast

value.dp_description:
The data collected through the AGPR provides an evidence base to assist entities to identify and progressively implement better property management practices, while also informing decisions in relation to whole-of-government leasing and property policy.

The data from the AGPR is used to develop cost indicators and private-sector performance benchmarking. These indicators help to provide a more complete picture of Commonwealth property performance and increase transparency around government expenditure on office accommodation.
value.dp_purpose: Whole of Government Property

value.dp_description: Requests from registered library users to view collection items onsite at the National Library. Collection items include books, journals, reports, magazines, maps, sheet music, oral histories, artworks, manuscripts, objects and ephemera. Each request includes information about the material requested, a time stamp and an optional note with further detail about the request.
value.dp_purpose: To facilitate Library user access to physical collection material onsite at the National Library of Australia. To provide information for collection use statistics and trends.
value.dp_title: Requests for physical collection material held by the National Library - 2003–current

value.dp_description: The Time Use Survey (TUS), conducted from November 2020 through to July 2021, measured the daily activities of people aged 15 years and over in Australia to provide insights into how people spent their time.
value.dp_purpose: To collect information to produce statistics by sex on how people use their time in Australia.

value.dp_description: Statistics on persons either held in adult corrective services custody or who are serving adult community-based orders in Australia.
value.dp_purpose: To produce statistics derived from information provided to the ABS from administrative records held by corrective services agencies within each state and territory. Statistics on federal prisoners are derived from records kept by the Criminal Law Division of the Australian Government Attorney-General's Department.

value.dp_description: The approved ex-manufacturer price (AEMP) for the pricing quantity of each PBS listed brand of pharmaceutical item, and if applicable the proportional ex-manufacturer price (PEMP) and claimed price for pack quantities.
value.dp_publisher: Department of Health, Disability and Ageing
value.dp_purpose: The National Health Act 1953 provides for ex-manufacturer pricing for the Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme from 1 October 2012. Prices are agreed or determined at the ex-manufacturer level rather than the price to pharmacists level (i.e. the approved ex-manufacturer price (AEMP) replaces the approved price to pharmacists (APP) as the core price in the Act).
value.dp_title: Approved ex-manufacturer price PBS pharmaceutical item pharmaceutical item
